main event: A single unidentified flying object was observed in the sky over Las Vegas, Nevada on July 21, 1963.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 7 minutes.
The object was described as having an erratic flight path, varying in speed, and appearing to oscillate and go out of sight.
The object was observed visually and through binoculars.
The report was filed by an employee at the Dunes Hotel in Las Vegas, who was described as reliable and cooperative.
The report was forwarded to the Scientific and Technical Division of the Air Force for evaluation.
witnesses: an employee at the Dunes Hotel
